I"<h2 id="themes">Themes</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Applying JavaScript &amp; jQuery in the DOM</li>
  <li>Using Websockets to dynamically update content</li>
  <li>Using AJAX to send and recieve content</li>
  <li>Diving deeper into SQL</li>
  <li>SQL scalability, performance, diagnostics, CLI</li>
  <li>Revisiting REST beyond CRUD (ex: workflows, search, etc)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="expectations-for-students">Expectations for Students</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Integrate JavaScript &amp; jQuery to meaningfully improve the user experience</li>
  <li>Implement websockets or equivalent technology to dynamically update data</li>
  <li>Isolate database/SQL weaknesses and improve them</li>
  <li>Add or improve a non-CRUD chunk of functionality with REST patterns</li>
  <li>Contribute to a non-Turing open source project</li>
</ul>

